{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8abbde9a-9062-411c-aa4d-f16f2ffb39dd","content":"**Exit code 8** is Microsoft.Testing.Platform's way of saying \"no tests were discovered.\" VSTest silently treated that as success.\n\nThe fix is the MSBuild property added to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>false</TestingPlatformExitProcessOnMissingTests>\n```\n\nThis tells the runner to exit with **0** instead of **8** when an assembly contains no tests. If you have many test projects, you can set this in a shared `Directory.Build.props` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26d452aa-fbf0-43e7-8a6d-b420eb22d11b","outputTokens":134,"requestId":"0828:1E7A6A:83368CC:9164885:69EABF90"},"id":"f3a77aaf-bfa5-4dfb-afcf-5dd71973efe3","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:55:48.760Z","parentId":"dfdaf20f-175b-45b2-9507-2bc390092ee6"}
